1
00:00:02,983 --> 00:00:06,937
It has to do with 
our ultimate aspiration,

2
00:00:08,135 --> 00:00:11,154
and also what separates human beings
from animals.

3
00:00:11,484 --> 00:00:13,361
[Star Wars & Eternal Story]

4
00:00:13,791 --> 00:00:19,013
We’re riveted to story, 
we’re hard-wired for story.

5
00:00:20,104 --> 00:00:24,433
That’s why to this day,
what’s been handed down in time,

6
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:27,565
when we say story 
we mean a narrative

7
00:00:27,565 --> 00:00:31,509
about who are people,
what is our purpose,

8
00:00:31,509 --> 00:00:34,391
what is our prospect 
or our possibility.

9
00:00:34,391 --> 00:00:36,886
And different stories speak to that.

10
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:39,957
That’s why human beings
are storytellers.

11
00:00:39,957 --> 00:00:42,673
Animals are not storytellers.

12
00:00:43,004 --> 00:00:45,825
Someone will try and say, 
“No, but dogs,

13
00:00:45,825 --> 00:00:48,350
they dream
about catching cats,

14
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:50,204
or cats dream 
about catching mice.”

15
00:00:50,204 --> 00:00:54,389
That’s another thing,
dealing with base necessities,

16
00:00:54,389 --> 00:00:56,361
eating, sleeping, sex, defense.

17
00:00:56,376 --> 00:00:59,761
Human beings, 
they’re interested in story

18
00:00:59,761 --> 00:01:02,892
that speaks to their heart
and their identity potential.

19
00:01:03,338 --> 00:01:06,759
What was popular
at one point were Star Wars.

20
00:01:06,928 --> 00:01:08,689
Let’s go back to that, 
it's still …

21
00:01:08,689 --> 00:01:10,834
everyone knows 
what Star Wars is.

22
00:01:10,834 --> 00:01:15,050
And we saw,
or the media observed, an almost

23
00:01:15,050 --> 00:01:20,469
religious-like following 
of those who were

24
00:01:20,469 --> 00:01:22,554
the devotees of it.

25
00:01:22,554 --> 00:01:27,444
And what was it about? 
The force, and the dark side,

26
00:01:27,444 --> 00:01:31,783
and the good side,
these very basic things

27
00:01:31,783 --> 00:01:35,610
that human beings deal with, 
good nature, bad nature.

28
00:01:36,442 --> 00:01:40,709
So, some people
will make the argument

29
00:01:40,709 --> 00:01:46,485
that these religious stories 
that you have in the various scriptures,

30
00:01:46,485 --> 00:01:53,510
in time philosophers try to translate that 
into something else,

31
00:01:53,510 --> 00:01:57,186
science came along, 
but still, you have

32
00:01:58,218 --> 00:02:01,458
film-makers of the 20th century,

33
00:02:01,458 --> 00:02:04,542
presenting these basic story models,

34
00:02:05,003 --> 00:02:09,047
that some people
will sometimes attribute to the Greeks,

35
00:02:09,047 --> 00:02:12,216
saying there’s only five, six,
seven stories that you can tell.

36
00:02:12,216 --> 00:02:15,826
It’s the same stories being reworked
in different ways,

37
00:02:15,995 --> 00:02:19,076
and people still find them fascinating,

38
00:02:19,076 --> 00:02:24,004
because it speaks
to their inner aspirations.

